{"lemma": "بَنانٌ", "slug": "بَنانٌ", "root": "ب.ن.ن", "root_slug": "ب-ن-ن", "root_link": "/words/roots/ب-ن-ن", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "بَنان", "root": "بنن", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n3317"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "fingertips", "fa": "نوک انگشتان", "ur": "انگوٹھوں کے نوک", "tr": "parmak uçları", "id": "ujung jari", "bn": "আঙুলের আগা", "es": "yemas de los dedos", "fr": "bout des doigts", "de": "Fingerspitzen", "ru": "кончики пальцев", "zh": "指尖"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "the fingertips or fingers", "tags": ["collective"], "examples": [{"text": "أَيَحۡسَبُ ٱلۡإِنسَـٰنُ أَلَّن نَّجۡمَعَ عِظَامَهُۥ ۝ بَلَىٰ قَـٰدِرِينَ عَلَىٰۤ أَن نُّسَوِّيَ بَنَانَهُۥ"}, {"text": "إن البنان الخمس أكفاء معا\nوالحلى دون جميعها للخنصر\nوإذا الفتى فقد الشباب سماله\nحب البنين ولا كَحُبّ الأصغر"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "banana", "tags": ["Arabic", "Mauritania", "Modern", "Morocco", "Standard", "collective"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From the root ب و ن (b w n), for the interstices between the fingers. Maybe also related to إِبْهَام (ʔibhām, “thumb”). The sense of bananas is from French banane."}, "ipa": ["/ba.naːn/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n3317", "headword_ar": "بَنَانٌ", "root": "bn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fingers;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSaAbiEu", "text_ar": "اَصَابِعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, Msb, K:) but whether it means peculiarly the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ASAbE", "text_ar": "اصابع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the hand, or those of the foot also, [i. e. the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is disputed: (TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ends,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extremities, thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K:) said to be so called because by their means are ordered those circumstances whereby man continues in existence; from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aban~a biAlomakaAni", "text_ar": "اَبَنَّ بِالْمَكَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) mentioned in the Kur viii. 12 because therewith one fights, and defends himself: (Er-Rághib, TA:) or it there signifies all the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "limbs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "members, of the body:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Aboo-Is-hák, M:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fingers,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toes, and any other parts of all the limbs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "members:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, TA:) or it means in the Kur the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$awaY", "text_ar": "شَوَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Lth, T, TA;) so in lxxv. 4; (M;) i. e. the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "arms"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hands"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "legs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "feet:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, TA:) accord. to El-Fárisee the meaning of the words in the Kur lxxv. 4 is, we are able to make their extremities like those of the camel, so that they should not profit by them in handicraft: (M, TA:) the n. un. is with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Lth, T, S, M, K;) meaning, accord. to Lth,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a single"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iSobaE", "text_ar": "اـِصْبَع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "finger,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toe"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; or, accord. to AHeyth, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whole"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ASbE", "text_ar": "اصبع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or, as some say, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "highest"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euqodap", "text_ar": "عُقْدَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "joint"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ASbE", "text_ar": "اصبع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (T:) the pl. of pauc. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAnaAtN", "text_ar": "بَنَانَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but a pl. of mult. is sometimes used as one of pauc.; and hence the saying of the rájiz,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "xamosa banaAnK qaAniy^i AlA^aZofaAri"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Five fingers,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ends of fingers, intensely red"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from the dye of hinnà"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the nails"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xamosFA mina AlbanaAni", "text_ar": "خَمْسًا مِنَ البَنَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAnN muxaD~abN", "text_ar": "بَنَانٌ مُخَضَّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fingers,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ends of fingers, dyed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "much dyed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with hinnà]; for every pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] between which and its sing., or n. un., there is no difference but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[added in the latter] may be treated as sing. and masc. (S.) Lth cites as an ex. of the n. un.,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "layosa liHaY~K fawoqahumo banaAnaho \n                      \n                     \n                        laAhum~a A^akoramota baniY kinaAnah"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O God, Thou hast honoured the sons of Kináneh: there belongs not to any tribe"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] excel-lence of the measure of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a finger above them."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "Msb", "K", "TA", "S", "Zj", "Lth", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}